<item>
            <title>[LU-16075] kernel update [RHEL8.6 4.18.0-372.19.1.el8_6]</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-16075</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Security Fix(es):&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;kernel: Small table perturb size in the TCP source port generation algorithm can lead to information leak (CVE-2022-1012)&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;kernel: a use-after-free write in the netfilter subsystem can lead to privilege escalation to root (CVE-2022-32250)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;p&gt;Bug Fix(es):&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Softirq hrtimers are being placed on the per-CPU softirq clocks on isolcpu&apos;s. (BZ#2090484)&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;enable/disable multiqueues repeatedly while ping local host, guest kernel panic (BZ#2093416)&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Backport kernel audit enhancements and fixes from v5.13-rc1 to v5.16-rc6 (BZ#2095434)&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;blk_update_request: I/O error, dev nvme0n3, during xfs creation (BZ#2100150)&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;SCSI updates for RHEL 8.7 (BZ#2100254)&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Kernel bug on mm/slub.c:314 (BZ#2102251)&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Implement new tc action for check_pkt_len (BZ#2102333)&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;too long timeout value with TIME_WAIT status of conntrack entry (BZ#2104002)&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Connectx6-DX, mlx5 , backport 087032ee7021 (&quot;net/mlx5e: TC, Fix ct_clear overwriting ct action metadata&quot;) (BZ#2104012)&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;mlx5: Software steering memory allocation failure, netperf TCP_CRR with ct(). (BZ#2104013)&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;tcp: request_sock leak in Calico OCP (BZ#2104670)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://access.redhat.com/errata/RHSA-2022:5819?sc_cid=701600000006NHXAA2&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://access.redhat.com/errata/RHSA-2022:5819?sc_cid=701600000006NHXAA2&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
